         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ You could easily fulfil the desire of Mr Young, ¶ See J. Young to M, 14 August 1877, in which he sought recognition for his exploring activities in Australia.M's note to Petermann is written on the...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">78.07.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To August Petermann</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sammlung Perthes Archiv,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">SPA ARCH<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">PGM<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">328</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Forschungsbibliothek Gotha der Universität Erfurt.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Petermann: 'Erh. 4. Sept. 1878' [Received 4 September 1878]. The letter is dated to early July 1878 as the latest possible date on which it could have been sent, to reach Gotha by early September. For a published version of this letter, see Voigt (1996), p. 134.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sie könnten dem Wunsche des Mr. Young leicht entsprechen, lieber Herr Professor, indem Sie ihn, als den Begleiter von Giles &amp; Tietkens in der 3ten Reise und als den Astronom u. Hauptsammler in irgend eine wissenschaftliche Gesellschaft aufnehmen liessen. Seine Adresse finden Sie im letzten Bande der R. G. S. von London.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Stets der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You could easily fulfil the desire of Mr Young,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See J. Young to M, 14 August 1877, in which he sought recognition for his exploring activities in Australia.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M's note to Petermann is written on the back of Young's letter.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>dear Professor, by having him admitted,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as companion of Giles<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ernest Giles.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp; Tietkens in the third journey and as the astronomer and principle collector, into some scientific society. You will find his address in the last volume of the R. G. S.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Royal Geographical Society.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of London.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
         </div>
